(24, '2014-03-13', 'The Student \r\n76 rue du Palais 1030 Bruxelles', 'Bruxelles - TTT liveshow', '<p><span class=\"fsl\">Avery Tinnitus<br /> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/AveryTinnitus\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/AveryTinnitus</a><br /> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sH6YElitphI\" target=\"_blank\">www.youtube.com/watch?v=sH6YElitphI</a><br /> <br /> Jon&aacute;&scaron; Gruska<br /> <span class=\"text_exposed_show\"><a href=\"http://jonasgru.sk/\" target=\"_blank\">http://mrkva.ovecka.be/</a><br /> <br /> Exoterrism<br /> <a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/exoterrism\" target=\"_blank\">http://soundcloud.com/exoterrism</a><br /> <br /> Prix libre<br /></span></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Avery Tinnitus</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"><br /> Strong and intriguing in it\'s meaning and form, this one time project is a thunderous tribute to our colliding sensations, to the rupture and tear that comes with an average tinnitus.<br /> Mysterious illness as well as a kind of synaesthetic blindness of hearing that is shared by all present.<br /> A grand piano suspended with an ambiguous imaginary future and immortal archive footage burned into a performance that twists and upsets predefined roles.<br /> The projectionist, on stage, handles the 16mm with deep care while he blinds the audience, giving a strong and beautiful illumination to music lost in<br /> a spectacular dynamic, hanging between the earth and the sky. Waiting for an inevitable meeting...<br /></span></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Jon&aacute;&scaron; Gruska<br /> <br /> Born in Czechoslovakia. He studied at Institute of Sonology in The Hague (Netherlands) and at Music Academy in Cracow (Poland). Works mostly with computers and electronics as a musician and sound artist in his projects Mrkva and Binmatu. He has authored interactive poems and visual performances, and is also a developer of open source computer instruments and artistic software. Gave workshops on city sonification and programming for artists.<br /> <br /> Performed and exhibited his work in Belgium, Czech Republic, Finland, Netherlands, Poland, Slovakia; on festivals such as Kraak (Belgium), Audio Art (Poland) or Next (Slovakia). In 2011 he started label LOM focused on East/Central European experimental art and music. You can bump into him in vegan restaurants or electronic component stores.<br /></span></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Exoterrism<br /> <br /> Exoterrism is a chinese fugitif, ex-shaolin, triad of WanChai (Hong Kong). He\'s mainly manipulating Feng Shui, QiGong, Chaotic functions, and Algorithms to produce unstable phenomenons between dimensions.<br /> His influences comes from radioactive frequencies, extra-sensorial perceptions, synaesthetics, post apocalyptic mayhem, the nasdaq stock market and the jungle.</span></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\"><a href=\"https://zvukolom.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://jg.zvukolom.org/</a><br /> <a href=\"http://jonasgru.sk/\" target=\"_blank\">http://mrkva.ovecka.be/</a><br /> <a href=\"http://binmatu.net/\" target=\"_blank\">http://binmatu.net/</a><br /> <a href=\"http://kraa.sk/mrkva/\" target=\"_blank\">http://kraa.sk/mrkva/</a><br /> <a href=\"http://ooo.merj.ch/\" target=\"_blank\">http://ooo.merj.ch/</a><br /> <a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/nikolamounoud\" target=\"_blank\">http://soundcloud.com/nikolamounoud</a></span></span><br /> <br /> More infos : <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1425294494384183\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/events/1425294494384183</a></p>', '13_03_2014_bruxelles_TTT_liveshow.jpg', 0),
