(26, '2014-03-22', 'OCCII\r\nAmstelveenseweg 134 \r\n1075 XL Amsterdam', 'Amsterdam - Algorave', '<p><strong>FIBER &amp; STEIM present: the first Dutch ALGORAVE!<span class=\"fsl\"><br /> <br /> </span></strong>On Saturday 22 March, FIBER and STEIM join forces to present the Netherlands&rsquo; very first Algorithmic Rave.<br /> <br /> If you\'re looking for a new kind of raw, unpredictable night of dirty industrial/techno sounds and truly live electronic music: this is it. No DJ\'s, no decks, no producers, no limits. The Algorave brings the cerebral world of live coding and the dirty dancing of raves together to form a new wave in club culture in which performers improvise their music live on stage by writing and rewriting code.<br /> <br /> Algoraves embrace the alien sounds of raves from the past, and introduces futuristic rhythms and beats made through strange, algorithm-aided processes. It&rsquo;s up to the good people on the dance floor to help the musicians make sense of this and do the real creative work in making a great party by providing the energy for the party.<br /> <br /> Not a coder? Don\'t worry: just like you don&rsquo;t have to be a guitarist to enjoy a rock concert, you don&rsquo;t have to know code to enjoy an Algorave. Everyone who is into new electronic music and underground raving will feel right at home.<br /> <br /> <br /> LINE-UP:<br /> <br /> - CANUTE (Alex McLean &amp; Matt Yee-King) (UK)<br /> --live drumming vs live coding<br /> --<a href=\"http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/canute/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/canute/</a><br /> <br /> - SHELLY KNOTTS (UK)<br /> --live coding performance<br /> --<a href=\"http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/shelly-knotts/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/shelly-knotts/</a><br /> <br /> - EXOTERRISM (BE)<br /> --live coding performance<br /> --<a href=\"http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/exoterrism/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/exoterrism/</a><br /> <br /> - LUUMA (UK)<br /> --live audiovisual coding<br /> --<a href=\"http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/luuma/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/luuma/</a><br /> <br /> - THE VOID POINTERS (NL)<br /> --custom-built instruments vs live coding<br /> --<a href=\"http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/void-pointers/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.codedmatters.nl/artist/void</a>-pointers/<br /> <br /> The event will also include two Supercollider workshops (on Friday 21 and Saturday 22) and a mini-symposium on Sunday 23.<br /> <br /> More information about this extra programme will be announced soon via <a href=\"http://www.codedmatters.nl/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.codedmatters.nl/</a>.<br /> <br /> Stay tuned!<br /> <br /> STEIM: <a href=\"http://steim.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.steim.org/</a><br /> FIBER: <a href=\"http://www.fiber-space.nl/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.fiber-space.nl/</a><br /> CODED MATTERS: <a href=\"http://www.codedmatters.nl/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.codedmatters.nl/</a><br /> Event page: <a href=\"http://www.codedmatters.nl/event/algorave\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.codedmatters.nl/event/algorave</a><br /> <br /> TICKET INFO<br /> <br /> Tickets are on sale via <a href=\"https://shop.ticketscript.com/channel/web2/start-order/rid/V3XFDKQE/language/en\" target=\"_blank\">https://shop.ticketscript.com/channel/web2/start-order/rid/V3XFDKQE/language/en</a><br /> <br /> <br /> The first Dutch Algorave also marks the 6th edition of FIBER\'s ongoing Coded Matter(s) programme, a series about the influence of code in art, music and design.<br /> <br /> Coded Matter(s) is supported by the Stimuleringsfonds Creatieve Industrie NL.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"fsl\"><span class=\"text_exposed_show\">More infos : </span></span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1406916009562778\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/events/1406916009562778</a></p>', '22_03_2014_amsterdam_algorave.png', 0),
